# Handle Missing Values
# For numerical columns: Fill missing values with the median
num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['float64', 'int64']).columns.difference(['country_code', 'Region', 'year'])
df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(df[num_cols].median())

# Standardize Numerical Columns (excluding 'country_code', 'Region', and 'year')
scaler = StandardScaler()
df[num_cols] = scaler.fit_transform(df[num_cols])

# Encode Categorical Variables (excluding 'country_code', 'Region', and 'year')
cat_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.difference(['country_code', 'Region', 'year'])

encoder = LabelEncoder()
for col in cat_cols:
    df[col] = encoder.fit_transform(df[col])

# Descriptive Statistics
# We are calculating stats excluding 'year', 'country_code', and 'Region' columns

df_no_categoricals = df.drop(columns=['year', 'country_code', 'Region'])
print(df_no_categoricals.describe())

# Group by 'Region' and calculate the mean for the relevant external debt columns
external_debt_columns = ['ExternalDebtStocks_LongTerm_CurrentUSD', 'PresentValue_ExternalDebt_USD']
region_external_debt_means = df.groupby('Region')[external_debt_columns].mean()

# Visualization of mean external debt values across regions
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

# Plotting for ExternalDebtStocks_LongTerm_CurrentUSD
region_external_debt_means['ExternalDebtStocks_LongTerm_CurrentUSD'].plot(kind='bar', color='skyblue', width=0.8, label='Long-Term Debt')
plt.title('Mean of External Debt Stocks (Long-Term) by Region')
plt.ylabel('Mean Value (USD)')
plt.xlabel('Region')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
